                                "rejectActorType": null
                            },
                            "body": "<P>I think you are looking for this support article: <A class=\"lia-external-url\" href=\"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/turn-off-copilot-in-microsoft-365-apps-bc7e530b-152d-4123-8e78-edc06f8b85f1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/turn-off-copilot-in-microsoft-365-apps-bc7e530b-152d-4123-8e78-edc06f8b85f1</A></P>\n<P>Note the instructions below only work for the client apps. You can not disable the icon in the web versions.&nbsp; Here are the instructions:<BR /><BR />Clear the \"Enable Copilot\" checkbox on Mac devices</P>\n<OL>\n<LI>In your app (for example, Word), select the app menu, and then go to&nbsp;<STRONG>Preferences</STRONG>&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;<STRONG>Authoring and Proofing Tools</STRONG>&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;<STRONG>Copilot</STRONG>.</LI>\n<LI>Clear the&nbsp;<STRONG>Enable Copilot</STRONG>&nbsp;checkbox.</LI>\n<LI>Close and restart the app.</LI>\n</OL>\n<P>Also you should note that if you are using an external mouse you can right click on a Mac.&nbsp; You just can't from the trackpad easily.&nbsp; Hope this helps</P>",
